'''Andrea Grobocopatel''' (born 18 March 1964) is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] economist, founding member of [[:es:Los_Grobo|Los Grobo]],<ref name="LoC">{{cite web|url=http://www.losgrobo.com.ar/|title=Los Grobo Agropecuaria: Juntos agregamos valor|website=www.losgrobo.com.ar}}</ref> a leading Argentine agronomic company and family business.<ref>https://www.cronista.com/empresas/Negocios-de-familia-Andrea-Grobocopatel-cuenta-las-claves-del-exito-20110208-0131.html</ref><ref>https://www.clarin.com/economia/Andrea-Grobocopatel-carta-oculta-Grobo_0_BJztC__vQe.html</ref>

At Los Grobo she held the position of CFO and was a member of the board where she advocated for the women leadership and inclusion in the company.<ref>https://www.cronista.com/pyme/El-libro-de-Andrea-Grobocopatel-Historia-de-vida-familia-y-empresa-20140522-0014.html</ref> She graduated from the University of Buenos Aires. Grobocopatel is a Cochran Fellow of the University of Illinois, and she is a shareholder and founder of agricultural and livestock company Ampatel. She is also Chairwomen of F.L.O.R. (Foundation for Responsible Leadership and Organizations)<ref name="LoC2">{{cite web|url=http://www.flor.org.ar/|title=Fundación FLOR|website=www.flor.org.ar}}</ref>. Flor's activities include training courses with the objective of women reaching decision-making positions.<ref>https://www.clarin.com/entremujeres/trabajo/capacitacion/mujeres-decision-trabajo-empoderamiento-liderazgo-capacitacion_0_rkJt04Jj.html</ref> and promoting women's financial independence.<ref>https://www.lanacion.com.ar/1990036-andrea-grobocopatel-tener-los-propios-ingresos-da-mas-libertad-para-elegir</ref> Grobocopatel is also a member of several advisory boards including the Advisory Board at University of Miami, the Advisory Board CEDEM (Women’s Economic Development Center) in Argentina’s Ministry of Production and a member of Marianne, French & Argentinian Women’s Association.{{cn|date=October 2018}}

Grobocopatel is an Argentine representative in the W20 forum in 2018, which forms part of the [[G20]] summit<ref name="LoC3">{{cite web|url=https://www.g20.org/en|title=G20 Argentina|website=G20 Argentina - Inicio}}</ref><ref>https://www.infobae.com/sociedad/2017/12/11/se-lanza-el-women-20-la-agenda-de-crecimiento-inclusivo-y-el-desarrollo-equitativo-del-g20/</ref><ref>http://www.lanacion.com.ar/2091839-los-desafios-de-las-argentinas-al-frente-del-w20-el-g20-femenino</ref> held in Argentina, and she stood as co-chair alongside Argentine businesswoman and member of the Argentine congress, [[Susana Balbo]].<ref name="LoC4">{{cite web|url=http://en.susanabalbowines.com.ar/|title=Home - Susana Balbo Wines|website=en.susanabalbowines.com.ar}}</ref><ref>https://www.infobae.com/sociedad/2018/04/06/andrea-grobocopatel-renuncio-a-la-co-presidencia-del-w20-el-grupo-de-genero-del-g20/</ref>
