'''Emil Harboe Eriksrud''' (27 January 1926 – 8 March 1990) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] businessperson and judge.

He graduated with the [[cand.jur.]] degree in 1949, and also took the average adjuster examination. He was a deputy judge in [[Nord-Troms District Court|Tromsø]], lecturer in jurisprudence at the [[University of Oslo]] and junior solicitor before becoming a barrister at the age of 34. In 1960 he was hired as a jurist in the corporation [[Hafslund (company)|Hafslund]]. In 1974 he attended the Advanced Management Program at [[Harvard University]].<ref name=obit1>{{cite news|title=Emil Eriksrud (obituary)|last=Aaser|first=Svein|authorlink=Svein Aaser|date=13 March 1990|work=[[Aftenposten]]|page=|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref name=sunnm>{{cite news|title=Navn i nyhetene|date=28 September 1988|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He became vice chief executive of Hafslund in 1976, and was the chief executive from 1979 to 1987. Among the important things to happen during his presidency was the acquisition of Actinor and thereby [[Nycomed]] in 1986. After retreating from Hafslund he served as presiding judge in [[Eidsivating Court of Appeal]] for some years until his death in 1990.<ref name=obit1/><ref name=obit2>{{cite news|title=Emil Eriksrud (obituary)|last=Berggrav|first=Dag|authorlink=Dag Berggrav|date=13 March 1990|work=[[Aftenposten]]|page=|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He chaired [[Kværner|Kværner Industrier]] from 1985 to 1986.<ref>{{cite news|title=C. Røtjer ny styreformann i Kværner|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|date=26 May 1986|language=Norwegian}}</ref> and [[Sunnmørsbanken]] from 1988<ref name=sunnm/> to 1989.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nye utfordringer for Borger A. Lenth|last=Warmedal|first=Morten Møller|date=13 March 1989|work=[[Aftenposten]]|page=18|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He was a supervisory council member of [[Kreditkassen]].<ref name=sunnm/> He was buried in [[Ullern]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disnorge.no/gravminner/index.php?language=engelsk|title=Cemeteries in Norway|publisher=DIS-Norge|accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref>

