'''Jean Claude Gandur''' (born 18 February 1949)<ref name=LPT>{{cite web|title=Profile: Addax and Oryx Group |url=http://laspalmastrader.com/wp/profile-addax-and-oryx-group-and-joyeux-anniversaire-monsieur-gandur/ |website=LPT |accessdate=6 November 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112180247/http://laspalmastrader.com/wp/profile-addax-and-oryx-group-and-joyeux-anniversaire-monsieur-gandur/ |archivedate=12 November 2014 |df= }}</ref> is a French-born Swiss businessman.
==Early life== Jean Claude Gandur was born in [[Grasse]], France in 1949.<ref name=Fg>{{cite web|title=Jean Claude Gandur|url=http://fg-art.org/en/jeanclaudegandur.html|website=Fg-art.org|accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref> Gandur studied law and political science at the [[University of Lausanne]] and history at [[Pantheon-Sorbonne University]].<ref name=Fg/>
